Step D-1 — Edit the Compose

Open the Run Summary / Log Summary Compose action in Section 8.
Click into the Inputs field. You should see existing lines like:

   BPs new: <varBPNew>
   BPs updated: <varBPUpdated>
   BPs removed: <varBPRemoved>
(Where <varBPNew> is a dynamic-content lozenge, not literal text.)
3. After the last BP line (BPs removed: ...), add a blank line, then add 4 new lines:
BPs BU resolved: <varBPOwningBUResolved>
BPs BU unmapped: <varBPOwningBUUnmapped>
BPs BU auto-created mapping: <varBPOwningBUAutoCreated>
BPs BU manual override skipped: <varBPOwningBUManualSkipped>
IMPORTANT — each <varBPOwningBU*> placeholder is a dynamic-content lozenge, not literal text. For each one:

Type the label text (BPs BU resolved: )
Then click the Dynamic content panel on the right
Find the variable under its appropriate section (Variables → search the name)
Click to insert as a lozenge

Repeat for all 4 lines.
Step D-2 — Mirror the L1-A07 grouping
If L1-A07 added a separator line or comment-style line before its Apps BU * block (like a blank line, or --- BU Resolution ---), mirror that pattern between the BP CRUD block and the new BP BU block. Just for readability in logs. If L1-A07 didn't, skip.
Step D-3 — Save
Save the flow.
